{
  "texts": [
    "These effects are sometimes packaged together in terms of an effective \"intervalley Hund's coupling\", but it is important to recognize that their energetics receives both Hartree and Fock contributions in generic HF states with IVC.",
    "The role of these terms is different at ν = -2, -3, so we discuss them separately (the generalization to the remaining fillings follow by stacking and/or particle-hole transformation.",
    ")At ν = -3, the states obtained by acting with SU (2) K × SU (2) K ′ × U (1) v rotations on the parent state in (107) can be parameterized in terms of the global U (1) v angle, as well as the individual spin orientations in each valley, nK and nK ′.",
    "The SU (2) K × SU (2) K ′ breaking terms then fix the relative angle between nK and nK ′foot_46.",
    "If these are antiferromagnetically aligned, we obtain a so-called \"spin-valley locked\" IKS state, which has IVC between opposite spin sectors, and as consequence exhibits a Kekulé spin texture rather than a Kekulé charge density.At ν = -2, the manifold generated by the SU (2) K × SU (2) K ′ × U (1) v action on the parent state in ( 108) can be parametrized in terms of the global U (1) v phase, the relative IVC phase 2γ between the two spin sectors, as well as a unit vector n that parametrizes the axis of spin quantization (note that n is redundant for the specific choice γ = 0 corresponding to a spin singlet)."
  ]
}